cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the problem of positioning in wireless networks. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it employs statistical problem formulations and MMSE estimates. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a distributed message passing algorithm for network localization. The paper also involves mathematical optimization, which could place it under cs.MA (Machine Learning) or cs.RO (Robotics).
